name: Santa Monica Cloud Computing Group - Footprints on the Moon
description: This group is for fellow cloud enthusiasts looking to push into uncharted territories of technology. All skill levels are welcome, some of the most innovating ideas can come from the least experienced. I started this group to meet other cloud computing users to gain knowledge and build a community here in Los Angeles. I have a great space for meetups where we can meet on a monthly basis. It doesn't matter if you are a developer, an IT admin, or just a curious observer, everyone adds value to the discussion of cloud computing.

name: Los Angeles MongoDB User Group
description: We are a group dedicated to increasing knowledge and awareness about MongoDB, an Open Source, document-oriented, NoSQL database. Please join us for our monthly meetings to explore this flexible and scalable alternative to traditional relational databases like MySQL, Postgres, SQL Server and Oracle.

name: Research Methods and Data Science Meetup
description:
This Research Methods and Data Science meetup group is devoted to make big data useful, and to promote big data technologies. It is a meet-up group bringing together people from research methodology, data science, data professional services, and computing in the greater Los Angeles area.

The focus of the group is about utilizing big data technologies to improve data analytics for social good, and to promote research methods and data science innovation. We plan to run workshops on big data analytics that can be applied to model and visualize open data and other complicated big data sets. Also, we will organize special meetings to discuss special data science projects, as well as data science automation and augmentation.

name: Los Angeles Google Analytics & Business Insights Training
description:
Los Angeles Google Analytics & Business Insights training is open to all business owners looking to increase their sales/leads/profit by understanding their website, their users and how those users interact with the site and their products. 

We offer FREE monthly webinars here: http://university.ppcmasterminds.com/courses/webby-replays. All webinars are also uploaded so you can watch them at your convenience.

We teach you how to use analytics and reporting tools to understand your visitors/users better - improving their experience, therefore increasing your conversion rates and sales. All speakers are respected in their industry and are well known for their subject matter expertise. Start growing your business and networking with other professionals in the Los Angeles area today!

Connect with us!

PPC Masterminds YouTube Page
PPC Masterminds Facebook

name: AdTech LA
description:
This is a group for anyone interested in scalable technology solutions helping to drive revenues for online advertising companies, ad exchanges and social networks. We are about scalable applications, big data, predictive analytics and data science. If you are a tech professional or an executive in any type of online advertising business: display, mobile, video, social or email, then this meetup is for you. 

We love to share and learn!

Welcoming all to this group!

name: DataForward
description:
DataForward is a gathering of professionals across industries who are passionate about data science, big data technologies, and data driven businesses. The group meets once a month at keynote events featuring talks and presentations by industry leaders. The DataForward events are hosted and organized by DataScience, and livestreamed to audiences all over the world.

The monthly events are dedicated to "big ideas in big data"- disruptive technologies, building data-driven culture, investment trends, and insights into how existing companies can unlock the value from their data. All events are free to attend.

Stay tuned as we announce speakers for our first keynote event in September.

name: Long Beach Python
description: The objective of this group is to get Pythonistas' together, to learn and share their experiences using Python as programming language and/or as data science tool-kit in various domains. Come join us to explore programming in general too. Suggestion on talks/discussion topics are welcome.

name: Reseda Homeschool sewing meetup.
description: We are a homeschooling group developing our sewing skills and having fun! New hand sewing projects are introduced weekly with special attention to stitches, fabric types, special projects , and patterns. Confidence is developed upon learning what we are capable of creating with our hands and ideas come about with a newfound joy in sewing. Sewing is such an expansive skill, learning the basics will give a good foundation for further development of all that sewing is. We are working on stitch books adding new stitches regularly. Everyone's ideas are integrated into the program. Let's get together and learn new skills ! Kids and moms or dads!

name: Couchbase Los Angeles
description:
What is Couchbase?

Couchbase is the company behind Couchbase open source project, a vibrant community of developers and users of Couchbase document-oriented database technology. 

Couchbase Server is a packaged version of Couchbase technology that’s available in Community and Enterprise Editions. Couchbase is known for easy scalability, consistent high performance, 24x365 availability, and a flexible data model. 

Companies like AOL, Cisco, Concur, LinkedIn, Orbitz, Salesforce.com, Shuffle Master, Zynga and hundreds of others around the world use Couchbase Server for their interactive web and mobile applications.

Sign up to our Couchbase Developer Newsletter

name: Los Angeles Marketing Analytics Group
description:
Los Angeles Marketing Analytics Group, sponsored and organized by eSage Group is a collection of marketers and analysts that want to share best practices and learn about new trends. We meet monthly on the 1st Tuesday at a cool location.

We talk Marketing Analytics from all angles, Attribution, Segmentation, Performance Optimization, ROI, Data Driven Marketing, Metrics, KPI's, Big Data, Internet of Things, and so much more.

We are very fortunate to attract some of the brightest marketers in the area to speak to our group! 

Join us to learn and network! We look forward to meeting you at our next one!

name: LA Big Data Analytics
description: This group is focused at learning, adapting and applying Big Data tools and technologies to distill information from big data.

name: Los Angeles Qumulo User Group (Max Q)
description: Max Q is a Qumulo user group. However, you don't need to be a current Qumulo customer to join us - VM/hardware eval'ers and storage enthusiasts are welcome! Meeting topics run the gamut from Qumulo product updates to user community "show and tell" -- see what others have done with their Qumulo clusters and how they've leveraged the API to build more efficient workflows. Max Q is also a great venue for users and enthusiasts to provide product/feature feedback -- help us build the world's best data-aware scale-out NAS! About Qumulo: Qumulo, headquartered in Seattle, pioneered data-aware scale-out NAS, which enables enterprises to manage and store enormous numbers of digital assets by building real-time analytics directly into the file system itself. Qumulo Core is a software-only solution designed to leverage the price/performance of commodity hardware coupled with the modern technologies of flash, virtualization and cloud. Qumulo was founded in 2012 by the inventors of scale-out NAS, and has attracted a team of storage innovators from Isilon, Amazon Web Services, Google, and Microsoft. Qumulo has raised $67 million in two rounds of funding from leading investors. For more information, visit www.qumulo.com.

name: CloudStack LA User Group
description: What is Apache CloudStack? Apache CloudStack is open source software designed to deploy and manage large networks of virtual machines, as a highly available, highly scalable Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) cloud computing platform. CloudStack is used by a number of service providers to offer public cloud services, and by many companies to provide an on-premises (private) cloud offering, or as part of a hybrid cloud solution. CloudStack is a turnkey solution that includes the entire "stack" of features most organizations want with an IaaS cloud: compute orchestration, Network-as-a-Service, user and account management, a full and open native API, resource accounting, and a first-class User Interface (UI). CloudStack currently supports the most popular hypervisors: VMware, KVM, XenServer and Xen Cloud Platform (XCP) and Hyper-V. Users can manage their cloud with an easy to use Web interface, command line tools, and/or a full-featured RESTful API. In addition, CloudStack provides an API that's compatible with AWS EC2 and S3 for organizations that wish to deploy hybrid clouds. Join the CloudStack Silicon Valley User Group Anyone is welcome! We will have talks from members of the foundation, committers, and users of CloudStack discussing various aspects of its development, history, architecture, operation and in general the direction of the project in this and upcoming meetups. And most importantly - how to get started on contributing yourself! Anyone is welcome to the group and we'll have beginner sessions available as well.

name: LA Cloud Computing
description: We are creative business professionals in the Cloud and IT space building a publicly accessible and cool grassroots Cloud network within the Los Angeles community.

name: Deep Learning | Los Angeles
description:
We are Southern California's largest consortium for Deep Learning / Deep Neural Networks.  We are open to all Data Scientists, Data Nerds, Machine Learning Specialists, and anyone interested in the field of Deep Learning in Machine Learning architecture and Data Science. 

If you are interested in organizing an event with us, or if you seek consulting services with regard to Deep Learning / Deep Neural Networks / Machine Learning, please write to one of the group organizers.  Your message will be answered as soon as possible.

name: LA Machine Learning
description: The LA Machine Learning Meetup began with events discussing a large variety of machine learning topics such as classification, clustering, neural networks, graphical algorithms, information retrieval, search, game theory, computational learning theory, reinforcement learning, collaborative filtering etc. More recently, a Data Science Track was launched with the focus on business applications and the entire process of data mining (e.g. business understanding, data collection, exploratory data analysis, data transformations, feature engineering, modeling, model validation, deployment, communication of results). While in fact Machine Learning is a part of Data Science and not the other way around, rather than starting a new meetup group, Data Science is featured within the already existing Machine Learning meetup.

name: Los Angeles AESA Computer Committee Forum
description:
The Los Angeles AESA Computer Group is a young community of like-minded Engineers, Scientists and Technologists who are working with or interested in Computers, Computer Science, IT Security, Cyber Security, IoT and related technologies. We plan on meeting regularly at least once a month, on the second Wed, for high level talks on the technology topics, share war stories, find solutions to difficult problems, help each other find jobs and to mingle and network together with fellow IT folks, technical managers, programmers, system admins, web developers. Contact us at aesacc2015 at gmail dot com

name: Data Science LA
description:
This meetup aims at bringing together data scientists, statisticians, business analysts, data miners, machine learning researchers, data engineers, software developers, data hackers along with startup co-founders, tech, business and analytics executives and anyone interested in extracting knowledge and business value from data.

Events might be cross-posted here though. Also check out our site datascience.la with materials from various data science meetups, interesting blog posts and much more.

name: Los Angeles Salesforce Developer Group
description: Can't get enough of Salesforce.com and the Force.com platform? You've come to the right place! This meetup is intended to serve the Greater Los Angeles area community of Salesforce.com(SFDC) and Force.com administrators, developers, power users, and other IT Professionals looking to expand their breadth of knowledge with like minded individuals. We will focus on development, but will focus on in-house business process development as well as 3rd party app development and ISV topics. We will cover not only Force.com standards such as Apex, VisualForce, SOQL and API's, but also integrations with external systems (i.e. Eloqua, Marketo, Oracle, SQL Server, Excel, etc.) Topics will be mainly driven by community needs, addressing how the tools of the Force.com PaaS can deliver rapid development to meet actual business needs (and a few useless cool tricks) for our local members. Come code, co-mingle, and collaborate!

name: Sports Analytics Hackers
description: Like Sports? Like Analytics? Like Hacking? If you like sports, data, analytics and technology and want to spend some time with like-minded geeks while watching a game, going to a game, or talking tech, we're looking forward to connecting and creating a community.

name: LA Chat Bot Meetup
description: This group is designed to bring people together from multiple disciplines to discuss conversational user interfaces. Messaging platforms are opening up their API's and creating their own "Bot Stores" to compete with the current App Stores. Conversational bots are not limited to SMS and messaging platforms. Virtual reality, augmented reality, robotics, and everyday hardware devices will incorporate some form of two-way communication via text or voice. It's a brave new world and we look forward to discussing the future and collaborating with like-minded hackers.

name: Our Lives, Our Data, LA
description: In this event series we explore our capacity to use the data we're immersed in to give back to our communities and enrich our lives.  We showcase experts and case studies for making positive impacts with data on personal, local and global levels. name: Southern California Julia Users

name: Southern California Sales Engineers
description: Whether you're called a Sales Engineer, Solutions Engineer, Pre-Sales Engineer, Technical Consultant or Solutions Architect, this is the meetup for you. For those of you interested in making the switch to the dark side from Software Engineering, Technical Account Management, or even as an Account Executive, feel free to have a look. Anyone who is in the California tech scene is more than welcome to join.

name: Los Angeles Quant Club
description: The Quant Club is for anyone interested in quantitative finance and machine learning. We are going to invite speakers to present their research. A special interest of the Quant Club is the application of machine learning tools for building quantitative trading systems. We are looking forward to meeting with you to jointly build trading systems using machine learning and other techniques.

name: Sports Colab LA - Intersection of Sports + Tech
description: Connecting the sportstech ecosystem of LA, Orange County and Southern California for monthly gatherings, including tech, startups, founders, developers, investors, sports biz, teams, leagues, athletes, media, venues and events in areas of sports, entertainment, media, digital health, fitness, fan engagement, wearables, IoT, sensors, VR, AR, streaming, video, data, analytics, social, mobile, apps, eSports, gaming, fantasy sports, e-commerce, ticketing and more.

name: Python Data Science LA
description: DataScience.LA is starting a Python for Data Science meetup! While the LA data science meetup scene has been dominated by R (mainly because of the LA R meetup one of us started 5 years ago), there are a lot of data scientists using Python. Our quick survey at the LA Machine Learning/Data Science meetup a few months ago revealed that most of the meetup's members are using R or Python, with R having only a very small lead. Therefore, to serve  all these Python users we need a Python for Data Science meetup! Also check out our site datascience.la with materials from various data science meetups, interesting blog posts and much more.

name: Hack Santa Monica Meetup

We will organize small-scale meetups to discuss what and how we can do to use existing Santa Monica open data, learn new ideas and data skills from each other, and present our works! We will also invite Santa Monica technology teams and even the mayor to come and join us!

You don't have to be a data genius to join us. Everyone is welcomed!

name: U.S. National Security & Intelligence- Sector Interest Group
description:
Is the U.S. National Security & Intelligence- Sector Interest Group (SIG) right for you?

Are you already an active cleared professional, in the Critical Infrastructure Sector of the Defense Industrial Base (DIB) or Intelligence Community?  Are you somehow connected to the U.S. National Security & Intelligence Ecosystem supply chain?  Do you interact with Washington, DC thought leaders on International Affairs or Foreign Policy issues? This group might be for you.

Does the DARPA Demo Day, Hacking for Defense (H4D) or the topics of Asymmetric Warfare or Lean LaunchPad Methodology interest you?  Are you ready to challenge your thinking?

Our monthly Executive Forum style-format will invite 8-12 "Thought Leaders" to share knowledge, insights and dialogue on a predefined problem set.  Your cohort peer group will be carefully selected to provide a diversity of thinking and relevant expertise at the event.

We will be meeting the 2nd Wednesday of each month (except Sep & Dec) from 8:30AM to 10:00AM in El Segundo, CA 90245.  Locations may change, as we gain new meeting sponsors for the SIG.

If your company or organization would like to sponsor an upcoming Cohort at your local business, hotel or a restaurant, please let us know.

name: Internet of Things Los Angeles - IoT LA

Thanks!

Tania

name: Pasadena Big Data User Group
description: "Big Data" is one of the most popular fields; however, it is also very diverse.  Many traditional data problems become more difficult when the data is at scale, and hence most people are only exposed to a narrow perspective of the whole picture.  This motivates us to start a big data user group to share knowledge and experiences from various big data specialties. Luckily, Pasadena is a great place to build such a community. In Pasadena we have many tech companies, research centers, incubators, schools, and even government support (Innovate Pasadena and JPL).  Moving forward, "Pasadena Big Data User Group" will not only host series of meetups, but also encourage people to build their networks and contribute on projects.  If you like the idea of what we are doing, feel free to contribute on https://hackpad.com/Pasadena-Big-Data-User-Group-o6glmgea2A7

name: LA Neural Network Aficionados

We strive to foster an open, innovative atmosphere for learning about and harnessing NNs.

name: Southern California Technology Careers N' Beers

We also sponsor local networking events like exclusive movie premieres, sporting events, and other unique events to bring together the tech community.

name: Graph Database LA
description: Developers interested in learning about and working with graph databases for social, spatial, hierarchical or other highly connected data sets. We host hands-on lab sessions, technology reviews, topical lectures, and plenty of social beer nights. Curious about graphs, want to pimp your non-RDBMS skills? Join us!

name: Sherman Oaks Online Marketing Meetup
description: We are focused on digital marketing strategies. From SEO to Social Media marketing, we are looking to connect with professionals who are experts in their fields. We will be hosting events to educate as well as provide networking opportunities.

name: LA Web/Mobile Software Entrepreneurs

name: Papers We Love, LA
description:
What was the last paper within the realm of computing you read and loved? What did it inspire you to build or tinker with? Come share the ideas in an awesome academic/research paper with fellow engineers, programmers, and paper-readers. Lead a session and show off code that you wrote that implements these ideas or just give us the lowdown about the paper (because of HARD MATH!). Otherwise, just come, listen, and discuss.

We're curating a repository for papers and places-to-find papers. You can contribute by adding PR's for papers, code, and/or links to other repositories.

If you need to reach out to us or have ideas for papers, just ask us via our twitter account. Papers We Love has a Code of Conduct. Please contact one of the Meetup's organizers if anyone is not following it. Be good to each other and to the PWL community!

Want to present?  Email us at paperswelove.la@gmail.com.  

Not sure where to start? Check out Sam's wishlist.

We're on Slack! http://papersweloveslack.herokuapp.com

name: Future Chief Data Scientists in Orange County, CA

name: Board of Games - Los Angeles

We will happily teach you, it's not hard. We play strategy games, card games, party games and deck building games. See you at our next event!

name: LA In-Memory Computing Meetup
description: If you need scalable, low-latency Big Data (think real-time analytics, logistics, telemetry, streaming data, etc.) then you need to get up to speed on In-Memory computing. Shuttling data back and forth to disks will simply no longer suffice in the age of Big Data. Luckily, costs for DRAM continue to drop, making In-Memory Computing on Big Data not only feasible, but absolutely necessary for companies stay competitive. This group is for people who want to get ahead of the Big Data curve through In-Memory Computing.

name: LA | Arduino+Raspberry Pi
description: This group is for anyone interested in learning, developing and building stuff with Arduino and Raspberry Pi. The main idea is to have talks and meetings about topics related with Arduino and Raspberry Pi. Also it would be great if we can take that further by working on projects and experiments/research. People from every level are welcome to join this group.

name: Google Cloud Platform LA
description:
This is a new Meetup in Los Angeles for people interested in Google Cloud Platform (GCP). We focus on giving members the opportunity to learn, discuss, and share with the rest of the GCP community in LA. And hopefully include some hands-on activities and events where members can discuss and hack on GCP and how we can leverage its cloud-based services and toolsets for real-world applications and topics such as cloud computing, microservice, Big Data, devops, Containers, etc.

Any skill level is welcome. Contact us if you are interested in speaking at or sponsoring this Meetup. Any feedback on content and demos greatly appreciated.

name: Los Angeles Cassandra Users
description:

name: Growth hacking & web scraping

name: Los Angeles Data Science
description:
Data Scientists in Los Angeles are doing incredible data science: making graph models of symptoms and human disease, extracting insight from huge amounts of data in real time, and building tools to make this whole process easier. We founded this Meetup as a forum to showcase that work.

This Meetup is organized by Galvanize. Looking to level up or make a career change? Learn more at: http://www.galvanize.com/courses/data-science/www.galvanize.com

name: LA Veterans in Technology

I started this group to meet and connect with other Veterans in the Tech space for networking and job seekers. I would love to have Tech companies human resources and recruiters come out to meet all the talented Veterans. We will meet once a month to cross ideas and new business owners can network. We can meet at the American Legion Post 43 in hollywood. It has a full bar and a great environment refreshments will be provided. name: Los Angeles / Santa Monica Mesos Users Group
description: This is the Souther California branch of the Mesos Users Group. We focus on helping people understand and deploy the Apache Mesos platform for creating hyperscale distributed systems. name: Los Angeles Redis Meetup

name: El Segundo Tech Community

Each month we have 1 major presenter, followed by 1-2 additional presenters showing demos of their technology, and networking. The idea is to promote new technologies to tech-interested public (as well as potential clients/employees) and provide networking opportunities. We seek sponsors and presenters!

name: ACM Los Angeles

Meeting topics are varied and range from tutorials on basic concepts and their applications, to success stories from local practitioners and academic students, to discussions of tools, new technologies, and best practices. All are welcome to attend, to meet others, and to present their work. ACM Los Angeles is officially a part of the ACM Local project of Association for Computing Machinery, Inc.

name: Predictive Analytics and Data Science using Spark, R, Python
description: We are technology enthusiasts from excited about emerging technologies. Analysts, Engineers, Students, Project Managers, and Managers who want to learn and pursue career in predictive analytics and data science are encouraged to join.

name: Hollywood Data Science Meetup - hosted by Logit

name: Los Angeles High Scalability Group
description: The L.A. High Scalability Group aims to be a Birds-Of-A-Feather style gathering of people working with big data, large scale and giant challenges in technology.

name: Tableau Users Group - Los Angeles

name: LA/Orange County Data Professionals Meetup - DAMA Chapter
description:
To provide a non-profit, vendor-independent association where data professionals can go for help and assistance. We are the local Chapter of DAMA-International: http://www.dama.org/


What this Meetup Group is about: Providing networking opportunities for the community of local data professionals, as well as speakers delivering technical content that will add to member job skills.


Who should join (Describe ideal members): The ideal member is working, or wants to work, as a data professional. Example job titles (either existing or desired) of such persons include: Data Architect, Data Strategist, Data Steward, Data Manager, Business Intelligence Specialist, Data Quality Officer, Data Modeler, Development DBA (Database Administrator). Those who deal directly with such persons, such as Project Managers, Business Analysts, and Product Managers, may also find some content to be of interest.


Why should they join, to learn, to share, or to have fun? To learn, and to share. This is a business, not a social, group.


What members can expect (Describe typical activities): Our typical activity is a weekday evening meeting, with optional networking and no-host dinner between 6:00pm and 7:20pm, followed by a speaker on a data-related topic from 7:30pm to 8:45pm, immediately followed by a Question & Answer period until 9:00pm.


Sample topics from the last few years include:


The Internet of Things

Data Virtualization: A Necessary Tool in Everyone's Data Integration Toolbox

Test-Driven Database Development

Big Data: A Critical Appraisal

Practical Experience in Starting a Data Governance (DG) Program

name: Los Angeles Machine Learning Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in machine learning, artificial intelligence, big data, training data, technology start ups and web / software development. All skills levels are welcome. I started this group to meet other machine learning enthusiasts. I look forward to exploring the art of artificial intelligence with everybody.

name: Artificial Intelligence and Character Animation LA
description:
This group is interested in the creation of "sentient animation"—interactive characters in VR, AR, games and apps who display social awareness and behavioral intelligence. Responsive, algorithmic personalities who use the familiar behaviors of living creatures to emotionally engage the viewer.

It's easy to imagine sophisticated and compelling “living characters” leveraging advances in machine learning, mind models, virtual and augmented reality, fast physics simulation, facial recognition, expression recognition, language processing, the semantic web, and good old manipulative animator trickery in the service of utility, entertainment, and emotional impact. 

The purpose of our meetup group—ideally a healthy mix of AI developers who love animation and animators who want to implement AI—is to find out what’s happening in this arena, share work and insights, and kick ideas around, hopefully while drinking beer. 

Over the next month I’ll be reaching out to find venues for our meetings, people who are interested in presenting, and possibly sponsors. If you can host or would like to present your work, please contact me!

name: TensorFlow Los Angeles
description:
Does TensorFlow have the potential to become the engine behind most successful consumer and industrial products of the next 10-20 years? 

Absolutely! A much better question is how, and in what new ways, can we:

a) train more computers to teach themselves by sifting through massive amounts of data coming out of all sorts of places

b) make these computers available through an API to provide a high-quality answer to anyone who is in need. 

Why? Because everyone in need deserves the right answer. 

So.... why don't we standardize & democratize the field with and around TensorFlow, and help change the world!?

What. We are a local micro community of those interested in advancing their knowledge of TensorFlow, its use cases and applications.

How. Join our group for a regular dose of human interaction, conversations, smiles, food and drinks on all things TensorFlow:

• How-To's & Best Practices

• Tutorials

• Models

• Algorithms

• Multi-GPU Autoscaling in the cloud

• Tools & Integrations

We will learn how others solve some of the hard problems that exist in the world around us, and how others make predictive APIs and  applications 

Join the movement. Let’s change the world. Because everyone in need deserves the right answer.

You are welcome:)

name: Apache Apex Next Gen Native Hadoop Big Data, El Segundo
description:
Welcome BigFoots!

This meetup has been formed to discuss customer use cases and design patterns related to Apache Apex, a next generation native Hadoop big data platform. We hope to build a community that meets face to face in El Segundo for folks interested in Apache Apex.

Apex unifies stream and batch processing. Use cases include ingestion, fast real-time analytics, data movement, disastor recovery in Hadoop, ETL, fast batch, alerts and real-time actions. Apex is a Hadoop-native YARN implementation. It simplifies development and productization of Hadoop applications by reducing time to market. Key features include Enterprise Grade Operability with Fault Tolerance, State Management, Event Processing Guarantees, No Data Loss, High Performance, Linear Scalability. Apache Apex enables users to run any user defined code natively in Hadoop. Apache Apex comes will deep versioned webservice and metrics for system and application monitoring. Additionally Apache Apex includes Apache Apex Malhar library of reusable operators (functions). Examples of connectors include the following

• Messaging Systems: ActiveMQ, Flume, JMS, Kafka, Kinesis Streams, MapR Streams, Nifi, RabbitMQ, Solace, ZeroMQ, etc.

• File Systems: HDFS, NFS, S3, etc.

• Databases/Stores: Accumulo, AeroSpike, Cassandra, CouchDb, MongoDB, HBase, Couchbase, Geode, HBase, Hive Tables, Impala, JDBC, HP Vertica, MemCache, MemSql, MySql, Oracle, Redis,  etc.

• Protocols: AMPQ, HTTP, FTP/SFTP, MQTT, SMTP, Rest/Soap, Twitter, Websockets, etc.

• Other Systems: Elastic Search, Solr, Twitter, etc. 

We want to develop a strong community that meets face to face and has a deep influence on big data ecosystem. If you are interested in presenting at this meet-up, please email to apex-meetup@datatorrent.com. 

Apache Apex Community Organizer

name: Big Data (native Hadoop) Ingest & Transform, Los Angeles
description:
Welcome! Big Data Ingesters,

This meetup has been formed to discuss customer use cases and design patterns for big data ingestion, transformation, and egression. Use cases for transformations include fast real-time analytics, data movement, disastor recovery in Hadoop, data integration, fast batch, and database load/off-load. Key focus will be on integrating Hadoop with various systems including Message Systems, File Systems, and Databases. Users should be able to connect to any source and any destination from within Hadoop. Ability to leverage any user code as part of the connections and transformations. We expect to develop a strong community in Los Angeles that meets face to face, and has a deep influence on big data ecosystem.

Examples of Messaging Systems include ActiveMQ, Flume, JMS, Kafka, Kinesis Streams, MapR Streams, Nifi, RabbitMQ, Solace, ZeroMQ, etc. Examples of File Systems include HDFS, FTP, NFS, S3, SFTP, MapR-FS etc.

Examples of Databases/Stores include Accumulo, AeroSpike, Cassandra, CouchDb, MongoDB, HBase, Couchbase, Geode, HBase, Hive Tables, MapR-DB, Impala, JDBC, HP Vertica, MemCache, MemSql, MySql, Oracle, Redis, etc.

Examples of protocols include AMPQ, HTTP, MQTT, SMTP, Rest/Soap, Twitter, Websockets, etc.

Other connectors include ElasticSearch, Splunk, Solr etc.

Our events will include production customer who will present their use cases.

We want to develop a strong community that meets face to face and has a deep influence on big data ecosystem. If you are interested in stepping up and leading organizing this meet-up, please email to ingest-meetup@datatorrent.com. 

Apache Apex Community Organizer

In short, we will be defining and detailing the specific skills needed to be competent. Therefore, if you feel that Cognitive Computing system design, development, and implementation is a strategic part of your career future, then come join our efforts. This is a we go, not an ego group. If you share our vision, and will work to help, then you are most welcomed; regardless of the current CC skill level. - Gary Deines on May 5, 2014.

name: Code Creator Meetup
description:
Who are we?

CCM is a FREE Code Creating Group in Orange County!

The CCM Code Creator Meetup started online in 2016 with a simple purpose: to allow people to work on software projects they've been dreaming about making and have a social life too.

We host computer language meet ups. It's a great opportunity to introduce yourself to new friends, work on projects you've been kicking yourself to start doing, and sharpen your skill sets. 

We also host meetups on members' requests. Let an event host know about any restaurants, events, or places you'd like to check out with us and we can arrange something. 

Group membership is free. If you'd like to sponsor us or advertise with us, please contact the organizer with more information. 

We're all about:

-Improving development skills 
-Making new friends 
-Sharing stories and experiences 
-Laughter and good energy

Who Should Attend?

If you are a software developer, like coding,  or are interested in becoming more familiar software development, whatever your level - This is the place to be.

Note, this is not a dating oriented meetup. Members are free to exchange contact information at their own disclosure, however CCM is not liable nor responsible for any interactions, engagements, or activities between members. 

CCM reserves the right to refuse membership to anyone without warning at its own discretion. 

When do we meet?

Check the meetup schedule for the next upcoming CCM event.

Is there a Fee?

Thanks to our lovely sponsors, membership is free. Our general meet up events have no cover charge. Depending on the meetup location, you may need to pay for your own parking.

So Are You In?

Whether you're looking to brush up on English or Japanese, all levels of proficiency are welcome. 

Join us today.

name: Apache Apex Next Gen Native Hadoop Big Data, Los Angeles
description:
Welcome BigFoots!

This meetup has been formed to discuss customer use cases and design patterns related to Apache Apex, a next generation native Hadoop big data platform. We hope to build a community that meets face to face in Los Angeles for folks interested in Apache Apex.

Apex unifies stream and batch processing. Use cases include ingestion, fast real-time analytics, data movement, disastor recovery in Hadoop, ETL, fast batch, alerts and real-time actions. Apex is a Hadoop-native YARN implementation. It simplifies development and productization of Hadoop applications by reducing time to market. Key features include Enterprise Grade Operability with Fault Tolerance, State Management, Event Processing Guarantees, No Data Loss, High Performance, Linear Scalability. Apache Apex enables users to run any user defined code natively in Hadoop. Apache Apex comes will deep versioned webservice and metrics for system and application monitoring. Additionally Apache Apex includes Apache Apex Malhar library of reusable operators (functions). Examples of connectors include the following

• Messaging Systems: ActiveMQ, Flume, JMS, Kafka, Kinesis Streams, MapR Streams, Nifi, RabbitMQ, Solace, ZeroMQ, etc.

• File Systems: HDFS, NFS, S3, etc.

• Databases/Stores: Accumulo, AeroSpike, Cassandra, CouchDb, MongoDB, HBase, Couchbase, Geode, HBase, Hive Tables, Impala, JDBC, HP Vertica, MemCache, MemSql, MySql, Oracle, Redis,  etc.

• Protocols: AMPQ, HTTP, FTP/SFTP, MQTT, SMTP, Rest/Soap, Twitter, Websockets, etc.

• Other Systems: Elastic Search, Solr, Twitter, etc. 

We want to develop a strong community that meets face to face and has a deep influence on big data ecosystem. If you are interested in presenting at this meet-up, please email to apex-meetup@datatorrent.com. 

Apache Apex Community Organizer

name: Los Angeles B2B Marketing Meetup
description:
Welcome to SoCal BMA's information page for our L.A. B2B Marketing Meetup Group.

Is this group right for you?  Please READ below:

Defining business-to-business (B2B):  Refers to business that is conducted between companies, rather than between a company and individual consumers (B2C).  B2B Marketing involves the sale of one company’s product or service to another company. B2B commerce transactions are between businesses, such as between a manufacturer and a wholesaler, or a technology company providing solutions to another company.

We are striving to build and maintain a substantive forum on B2B Marketing and Communications within this group. If you do not work in the B2B space, as described above, we ask you, please do not request to join this group.

Business Marketing Association, Southern California Chapter (SoCal BMA) provides a wide range of events, resources and opportunities to help B2B marketers meet the daily challenges of sustaining business profitability and enhancing their development as B2B marketing professionals. No other organization delivers the same level of commitment to the information and peer networking needs of business leaders, company marketers and communicators.

From executive round tables to panel discussions to online events, SoCal BMA serves its B2B marketing community through education, professional development, and peer networking. As a business marketer or communicator, your needs are distinct from those of the consumer marketing environment. SoCal BMA focuses on meeting the challenges presented in business marketing and communications, day in and day out.

Is this the right group for you?
Defining business-to-business (B2B):  Commerce transactions between businesses, such as between a manufacturer and a wholesaler.

What this group is not about:
This Los Angeles B2B Marketing Meetup Group is not intended for consumer products/services professionals such as financial planners, personal/auto insurance sales/consulting -- nor direct sales professionals (multi-level, network marketing). We are confident that you will find a number of other Meetup Groups that can better facilitate those specific interests and business needs.

Who should join this group?
B2B marketers and communicators.

We hope the above information has been helpful for you at determining if this group is or is not the right group for you.

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

GROUP RULES

• This group is intended to facilitate the B2B marketing community in Los Angeles, part of our BMA Southern California Chapter's region. Comments must be related to our SoCal BMA postings and/or to B2B marketing and communications matters.

• This group is not for the promotion or solicitation of products or services to members of this group.

• Disregarding the Group Rules will unfortunately lead to your removal from this group.

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
To learn more about SoCal BMA, visit our website.

name: Stacki LA
description:
Stacki LA is a meetup for those interested in learning about Stacki, server provisioning, configuration management, and DevOps.  This group is for everyone- both Stacki users and beginners to Stacki- you don't need to have any prior experience!
Stacki is an open source CentOS/RHEL bare metal provisioning tool that can take your servers from bare hardware (or virtual hardware) to working Linux, ready to install applications. Stacki does this at scale, so deploying 1000+ servers is no more complex than deploying one. Once your servers are installed with Stacki, you can augment them with configuration tools like Puppet, Chef, Salt, CFEngine, Ansible, etc.   

Join the Stacki community: https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/stacki

Download Stacki: http://www.stacki.com/

Stacki documentation: https://github.com/StackIQ/stacki/wiki

Follow Stacki on Twitter: https://twitter.com/Stacki

name: Hardware the easy way. A meeting of strategists
description: There are many challenges we face in the many roles within the IT industry. This group is focused on discussing and solving the challenges that we come across while dealing with enterprise IT hardware. Many groups and clubs spread their solutions too thin and the discussion becomes generalized. You can expect to participate and discuss some of the following topics (and more, of course): * Ideas and solutions for IT Hardware Management * Procurement the smart way - unbiased and not dependent on marketing * Cost saving without changing the process * Realizing full potential and value of your infrastructure * Deep insight into the back-end of the hardware industry (manufacturing, targeted logistics etc) * E-Waste? Lots to discuss and even more myths to bust If those sound like interesting topics or if you feel like you can bring ideas and value to the group, we'd be happy to see you! Oh yeah... this is a big one: All events will be courteously paid for via our sponsors. Grab your thinking cap and your beer sleeve. Together, we can achieve more.
